                        <interp inst="t18600507-name-728" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES LUSCOMBE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>). There was a good deal of blood on the front of the last witness's shawl—it came from the cut on her nose and eye<lb></lb>brow, and there was a little bit of a scar on her cheek.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did you hold the light to her face? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes; there was not the least bit of mark to be seen on the prisoner's face—the blood on the shawl was quite fresh—the charge was refused at the station—I showed the blood there, and the woman showed her nose.</p>
